            <h3>About ISBNs</h3>
            <p>An ISBN is a unique identifier for books and other publicati=
ons. ISBN-10 was used until 2007, after which ISBN-13 became the standard. =
Both formats are still considered valid.</p>
            <p><strong>ISBN-10 format:</strong> X-XXXX-XXXX-X<br>
            <strong>ISBN-13 format:</strong> XXX-X-XXXX-XXXX-X</p>
            <p>Where X represents a digit (0-9) or, in the case of ISBN-10,=
 the last character can also be 'X' representing the number 10.</p>
